I’ve got the likely fix shape: remove ABI-decoding assumptions against the gateway, scan the known preloaded route range with low-level `getRoute`/`routes`/`addressAt` fallbacks, and make native-profit accounting use the canonical `0xEeee…` sentinel instead of `address(0)`. I’m applying that now so the exploit path stays the same but the verifier stops failing on empty-return introspection.
